PN,41401
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1774102278
OL,3,CKing Harold's forced march to Battle
OL,4,Cof Hastings 'implausible'
OL,6,FA near 200-mile forced march to the
OL,7,FBattle of Hastings in 1066 did not
OL,8,Fhappen, research suggests, with troops
OL,9,Flargely travelling by ship.
OL,11,FIt has long been taught that after
OL,12,FKing Harold's victory at the Battle of
OL,13,FStamford Bridge in Yorkshire, there
OL,14,Fwas a forced march south for his army
OL,15,Fto face the Norman invasion.
OL,17,FHowever, University of East Anglia
OL,18,Fprofessor of medieval history and
OL,19,Fliterature Tom Licence argues that
OL,20,Fthis was down to a Victorian
OL,21,F"misunderstanding".
OL,26,@}D@AOU}D@RO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
